# Frontend Rules

- Prefer functional components and hooks.
- Extract reusable behavior into custom hooks before duplicating component logic.
- Keep components focused: container components orchestrate data, presentational components render UI.
- Use semantic HTML and keyboard-accessible interactions by default.
- Include loading, empty, and error states for data-driven screens.
- Avoid premature abstraction; refactor shared patterns after the second concrete use case.
- Keep route-level code split points where practical.
